fix: ship translator/ as wheel package and return Path for mono_pdf_path

- pyproject: project name `doc-translator` normalises to `doc_translator`,
  which hatchling searched for as the default package dir. Since the
  actual source lives under `translator/`, the editable build failed in
  CI with "Unable to determine which files to ship inside the wheel".
  Add explicit `[tool.hatch.build.targets.wheel] packages = ["translator"]`.
- word.py / excel.py: gui.py calls `mono_path.exists()` on the result's
  `mono_pdf_path`, so the field must be a `Path | None`, not `str | None`.
  Update both result dataclasses and pass `output_path` (Path) through
  instead of `str(output_path)`.
